version_description: Mine is a simple chord version that sounds as accurate as possible for beginners.
An amalgamation of version 5 and 3 with correct chords.
Pinegrove playing Cadmium live at Audiotree.
Made this tab because there wasn't any other version on here of this song.
Acoustic live version with detailed chord breakdowns.
I love this song and there was only a Chordify version and I hate that website. I tried transcribing it over to here, but I think someone else could do a much better job.
My version is different because the chords used are written out and they are placed where they are played in the song.
This tab is is based off this version of the song: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eY5q1XwPLCE.

Watch/listen to the video/song for a strumming pattern and how many times to play each chord. All the chords you need to play it the way Evan always does live, along with a tab for small lead inflections in the intro to spice it up a bit. So the chords already on here aren't exactly what Evan plays live although they sound like they work if you don't have a capo. These chords are taken from this live acoustic session https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0PRM98eMVgU and Evan also plays it the same way on their NPR Music Tiny Desk concert https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=weL8HTY1NJU.
